# harness allowlist
#
# One host per line. Blank lines and lines starting with `#` are comments.
# Inline `# git-push` annotation on a host enables `git push` to that host
# (the firewall will configure the `store` credential helper for it). Without
# the annotation, `git pull` works but `git push` fails — the default for new
# installs.
#
# This file is read by every harness container at startup. Hosts here are
# resolved to IPs and added to an ipset; any other outbound traffic is
# rejected with icmp-admin-prohibited.
#
# To edit: `harness net` (B2) or edit `<install-root>/.harness-allowlist`
# directly and `harness restart` to reload.

# === Package registries ===
pypi.org
files.pythonhosted.org
registry.npmjs.org

# === GitHub ===
# github.com is pull-only by default. Add `# git-push` after the host name to
# enable push (you'll still need credentials in $HOME/.git-credentials).
github.com
api.github.com
codeload.github.com
raw.githubusercontent.com
objects.githubusercontent.com

# === Claude Code connectivity probe (NOT enabled by default) ===
# Note: claude-code probes api.anthropic.com on startup and prints the cosmetic
# warning "Unable to connect to Anthropic services" if the probe is blocked.
# The warning is purely cosmetic — chat traffic flows through ollama via
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL and never touches Anthropic. We deliberately leave the
# probe blocked so that the harness keeps zero outbound traffic to Anthropic.
# Uncomment the following line to silence the warning if you find it noisy:
#   api.anthropic.com

# === ADD YOUR UPSTREAM LLM API HOSTNAME HERE ===
# The hostname must match the host portion of PROXY_API_URL — the firewall
# will refuse to start if PROXY_API_URL points at a host that isn't on this
# list. Uncomment whichever you use, or add your own.
# api.openai.com
# generativelanguage.googleapis.com

# === ADD YOUR SELF-HOSTED GIT REMOTES HERE (with `# git-push` if needed) ===
# my-gitlab.example.com   # git-push
# git.internal.corp       # git-push
